Good, I now have a complete picture of the project. Here is the full implementation plan.

---

# Profreach Implementation Plan

## Project Summary

A professor outreach tracker for graduate school applications built on Next.js 16.1.6 with App Router, TypeScript, React 19, Tailwind CSS v4, and Gemini API. All data lives in localStorage behind an abstraction layer. Four pages: Dashboard, Professor Detail, Profile, and Data Export.

---

## Phase 0: Project Setup and Dependencies

**Goal:** Install all packages, initialize shadcn/ui, set up project scaffolding.

### Step 0.1 -- Install packages

Run via pnpm:

```
pnpm add @google/generative-ai uuid lucide-react sonner
pnpm add -D @types/uuid
```

### Step 0.2 -- Initialize shadcn/ui

```
pnpm dlx shadcn@latest init
```

During init, select:
- Style: New York
- Base color: Zinc (or Neutral -- pick what fits your "distinctive" design goal)
- CSS variables: yes

This will create:
- `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/components.json`
- `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/lib/utils.ts` (cn utility)
- Updates to `globals.css` with CSS variables

### Step 0.3 -- Install shadcn/ui components

Install all needed components upfront:

```
pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add button input label textarea select badge card dialog dropdown-menu tabs separator scroll-area sheet tooltip avatar command popover skeleton toast
```

### Step 0.4 -- Create `.env.local`

```
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_key_here
```

Update `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/.gitignore` to include `.env.local` (Next.js already does this by default).

### Step 0.5 -- Update `next.config.ts`

Add `serverExternalPackages` if needed for any server-side only libs. At minimum, ensure experimental features are ready.

### Commit: "chore: install dependencies and initialize shadcn/ui"

---

## Phase 1: Foundation Layer -- Types, Storage, and Layout

**Goal:** Build the data types, storage abstraction, layout shell with navigation, and theme setup.

### File Structure Created in This Phase

```
app/
  layout.tsx                    -- (update) root layout with sidebar/nav
  globals.css                   -- (update) design tokens, custom styles
  page.tsx                      -- (replace) dashboard page
  professor/
    [id]/
      page.tsx                  -- professor detail (placeholder)
  profile/
    page.tsx                    -- profile page (placeholder)
  export/
    page.tsx                    -- export page (placeholder)
  api/
    gemini/
      lookup/route.ts           -- professor lookup endpoint
      email/route.ts            -- email drafting endpoint  
      chat/route.ts             -- chat endpoint
      resume/route.ts           -- resume parsing endpoint
      memory/route.ts           -- memory extraction endpoint
lib/
  types.ts                      -- all TypeScript interfaces
  storage.ts                    -- localStorage abstraction layer
  constants.ts                  -- statuses, templates, categories
  gemini.ts                     -- server-side Gemini client init
  utils.ts                      -- (already created by shadcn) + custom helpers
components/
  layout/
    sidebar.tsx                 -- main navigation sidebar
    header.tsx                  -- page header with breadcrumbs
    app-shell.tsx               -- wraps sidebar + content area
  ui/                           -- (shadcn components, auto-generated)
  providers.tsx                 -- client-side providers (toast, etc.)
hooks/
  use-storage.ts                -- React hook wrapping storage service
  use-debounce.ts               -- debounce hook for search
```

### 1.1 -- Type Definitions

**File: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/lib/types.ts`**

Define all interfaces:

```typescript
// Application status enum
export const APPLICATION_STATUSES = [
  'Not Contacted', 'Researching', 'Email Drafted', 'Email Sent',
  'Followed Up', 'Responded', 'Interview Scheduled',
  'Applied to Lab', 'Accepted', 'Rejected', 'On Hold'
] as const;
export type ApplicationStatus = typeof APPLICATION_STATUSES[number];

// Hiring status
export type HiringStatus = 'yes' | 'no' | 'unknown';

// Document categories
export const DOCUMENT_CATEGORIES = [
  'Resume', 'Transcript', 'SOP', 'LOR', 'Other'
] as const;
export type DocumentCategory = typeof DOCUMENT_CATEGORIES[number];

// Email templates
export const EMAIL_TEMPLATES = ['cold', 'followup', 'thankyou'] as const;
export type EmailTemplate = typeof EMAIL_TEMPLATES[number];

export interface Professor {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  email: string;
  university: string;
  department: string;
  country: string;
  researchAreas: string[];
  hiringStatus: HiringStatus;
  hIndex: number | null;
  googleScholarUrl: string;
  labUrl: string;
  profileUrl: string;
  keyPublications: { title: string; url: string }[];
  notes: string;
  status: ApplicationStatus;
  lastContactDate: string | null;
  createdAt: string;
  updatedAt: string;
}

export interface Profile {
  name: string;
  email: string;
  university: string;
  degreePursuing: string;
  researchInterests: string[];
  bio: string;
  resumeBase64: string | null;
  resumeFileName: string | null;
}

export interface Document {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  category: DocumentCategory;
  fileBase64: string;
  fileName: string;
  mimeType: string;
  uploadedAt: string;
}

export interface MemoryItem {
  id: string;
  content: string;
  sourceProfessorId: string | null;
  sourceProfessorName: string | null;
  tags: string[];
  createdAt: string;
}

export interface ChatMessage {
  id: string;
  professorId: string;
  role: 'user' | 'assistant';
  content: string;
  createdAt: string;
}

export interface EmailDraft {
  professorId: string;
  content: string;
  template: EmailTemplate;
  lastGeneratedAt: string | null;
  lastEditedAt: string;
}

// The full export shape
export interface AppData {
  professors: Professor[];
  profile: Profile;
  documents: Document[];
  memory: MemoryItem[];
  chats: Record<string, ChatMessage[]>; // keyed by professorId
  drafts: Record<string, EmailDraft>;   // keyed by professorId
}
```

### 1.2 -- Constants

**File: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/lib/constants.ts`**

Contains status color mappings, default profile, sort options, filter definitions. For example:

```typescript
export const STATUS_COLORS: Record<ApplicationStatus, string> = {
  'Not Contacted': 'bg-gray-100 text-gray-700',
  'Researching': 'bg-blue-100 text-blue-700',
  'Email Drafted': 'bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-700',
  'Email Sent': 'bg-orange-100 text-orange-700',
  'Followed Up': 'bg-purple-100 text-purple-700',
  'Responded': 'bg-green-100 text-green-700',
  'Interview Scheduled': 'bg-teal-100 text-teal-700',
  'Applied to Lab': 'bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700',
  'Accepted': 'bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-800',
  'Rejected': 'bg-red-100 text-red-700',
  'On Hold': 'bg-amber-100 text-amber-700',
};

export const DEFAULT_PROFILE: Profile = {
  name: '', email: '', university: '', degreePursuing: '',
  researchInterests: [], bio: '', resumeBase64: null, resumeFileName: null
};

export const SORT_OPTIONS = [
  { label: 'Name', value: 'name' },
  { label: 'University', value: 'university' },
  { label: 'Date Added', value: 'createdAt' },
  { label: 'Last Contact', value: 'lastContactDate' },
] as const;
```

### 1.3 -- Storage Abstraction Layer

**File: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/lib/storage.ts`**

This is the most architecturally important file. It wraps localStorage behind a clean API so a future database migration only changes this one file.

Design principles:
- Each "collection" (professors, documents, memory, chats, drafts) gets its own localStorage key: `profreach_professors`, `profreach_profile`, etc.
- All reads/writes go through helper functions that handle JSON serialization.
- Every mutation triggers a `CustomEvent` on `window` so React hooks can re-render.

```typescript
const STORAGE_KEYS = {
  professors: 'profreach_professors',
  profile: 'profreach_profile',
  documents: 'profreach_documents',
  memory: 'profreach_memory',
  chats: 'profreach_chats',
  drafts: 'profreach_drafts',
} as const;

const STORAGE_EVENT = 'profreach-storage-update';

function read<T>(key: string, fallback: T): T { ... }
function write<T>(key: string, data: T): void { ... dispatch event }

export const storage = {
  professors: {
    getAll(): Professor[] { return read(STORAGE_KEYS.professors, []); },
    getById(id: string): Professor | undefined { ... },
    create(data: Omit<Professor, 'id' | 'createdAt' | 'updatedAt'>): Professor { ... },
    update(id: string, data: Partial<Professor>): Professor { ... },
    delete(id: string): void { ... },
  },
  profile: {
    get(): Profile { return read(STORAGE_KEYS.profile, DEFAULT_PROFILE); },
    update(data: Partial<Profile>): Profile { ... },
  },
  documents: {
    getAll(): Document[] { ... },
    create(doc: Omit<Document, 'id' | 'uploadedAt'>): Document { ... },
    delete(id: string): void { ... },
  },
  memory: {
    getAll(): MemoryItem[] { ... },
    add(item: Omit<MemoryItem, 'id' | 'createdAt'>): MemoryItem { ... },
    update(id: string, data: Partial<MemoryItem>): MemoryItem { ... },
    delete(id: string): void { ... },
    search(query: string): MemoryItem[] { ... }, // simple text match
  },
  chats: {
    getByProfessorId(professorId: string): ChatMessage[] { ... },
    addMessage(professorId: string, message: Omit<ChatMessage, 'id' | 'createdAt'>): ChatMessage { ... },
    clearByProfessorId(professorId: string): void { ... },
  },
  drafts: {
    getByProfessorId(professorId: string): EmailDraft | null { ... },
    save(professorId: string, data: Partial<EmailDraft>): EmailDraft { ... },
  },
  exportAll(): AppData { ... },
  importAll(data: AppData): void { ... },
};
```

### 1.4 -- React Hook for Storage

**File: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/hooks/use-storage.ts`**

```typescript
'use client';
// Listens for the custom storage event and returns reactive data.
// Example: const professors = useStorageCollection(() => storage.professors.getAll());
// Automatically re-renders when storage changes.
export function useStorageData<T>(getter: () => T): T { ... }
```

Uses `useSyncExternalStore` for safe concurrent React 19 usage. The subscribe function listens for the `profreach-storage-update` event on `window`.

### 1.5 -- Debounce Hook

**File: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/hooks/use-debounce.ts`**

Standard debounce hook for search input, 300ms default.

### 1.6 -- App Layout and Navigation

**File: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/components/layout/sidebar.tsx`** (client component)

A vertical sidebar with navigation links:
- Dashboard (Home icon) -- `/`
- Profile (User icon) -- `/profile`
- Export (Download icon) -- `/export`

Use `lucide-react` icons. Highlight active route using `usePathname()`.

**File: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/components/layout/header.tsx`** (server component)

A top bar per page showing page title. Each page passes its own title.

**File: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/components/layout/app-shell.tsx`** (server component)

Wraps sidebar + main content area in a flex layout. The sidebar is fixed-width on the left, content scrolls independently.

**File: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/components/providers.tsx`** (client component)

Wraps `children` with the `<Toaster />` from sonner (for toast notifications).

**Update: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/app/layout.tsx`**

- Update metadata title/description to "Profreach"
- Keep Geist fonts
- Wrap `{children}` in `<Providers>` and `<AppShell>`
- Update `globals.css` with design tokens for a distinctive look (custom accent color, refined spacing)

**Update: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/app/globals.css`**

- Keep the Tailwind v4 `@import "tailwindcss"` and `@theme inline` block
- Add custom color variables for the Profreach brand (a warm accent color like amber/orange or a scholarly blue-violet)
- Add custom scrollbar styles, selection color, focus ring overrides

### Commit: "feat: add type definitions, storage layer, layout shell, and navigation"

---

## Phase 2: Dashboard Page

**Goal:** Build the main professor list view with search, filtering, sorting, and the "Add Professor" input.

### Files

```
app/
  page.tsx                                -- dashboard server wrapper
components/
  dashboard/
    professor-list.tsx                    -- client: renders professor cards
    professor-card.tsx                    -- client: single professor card
    add-professor-input.tsx               -- client: input + Gemini lookup
    add-professor-dialog.tsx              -- client: review/edit before saving
    filter-bar.tsx                        -- client: filter/sort/search controls
    status-badge.tsx                      -- shared status badge component
    dashboard-stats.tsx                   -- summary stats at top
app/
  api/
    gemini/
      lookup/route.ts                    -- POST: professor lookup
```

### 2.1 -- Gemini Server Client

**File: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/lib/gemini.ts`**

```typescript
import { GoogleGenerativeAI } from '@google/generative-ai';

const genAI = new GoogleGenerativeAI(process.env.GEMINI_API_KEY!);

export function getGeminiModel(modelName = 'gemini-2.0-flash') {
  return genAI.getGenerativeModel({ model: modelName });
}

// For search-grounded lookups
export function getGroundedModel() {
  return genAI.getGenerativeModel({
    model: 'gemini-2.0-flash',
    tools: [{ googleSearchRetrieval: {} }],
  });
}
```

### 2.2 -- Professor Lookup API Route

**File: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/app/api/gemini/lookup/route.ts`**

- Accepts POST with `{ query: string }` (name+university or URL)
- Uses the grounded Gemini model
- System prompt instructs Gemini to return a structured JSON matching the `Professor` shape (minus id, createdAt, updatedAt, status)
- Parses the JSON from Gemini's response, validates it, returns it
- Error handling for rate limits, malformed responses

### 2.3 -- Dashboard Page

**File: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/app/page.tsx`**

This is a server component that renders the page shell. It imports the client components:

```tsx
import { Suspense } from 'react';
import { DashboardStats } from '@/components/dashboard/dashboard-stats';
import { AddProfessorInput } from '@/components/dashboard/add-professor-input';
import { FilterBar } from '@/components/dashboard/filter-bar';
import { ProfessorList } from '@/components/dashboard/professor-list';

export default function DashboardPage() {
  return (
    <div className="space-y-6">
      <h1>Dashboard</h1>
      <DashboardStats />
      <AddProfessorInput />
      <FilterBar />
      <ProfessorList />
    </div>
  );
}
```

All the child components are `'use client'` because they read from localStorage.

### 2.4 -- Add Professor Input

**File: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/components/dashboard/add-professor-input.tsx`**

- Input field + "Lookup" button
- On submit, calls `/api/gemini/lookup` with the query
- Shows loading spinner during fetch
- On success, opens `AddProfessorDialog` with pre-filled data

**File: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/components/dashboard/add-professor-dialog.tsx`**

- Dialog/Sheet showing all professor fields pre-filled from Gemini
- User reviews, edits any fields
- "Save" button calls `storage.professors.create()`
- Toast notification on success

### 2.5 -- Filter Bar

**File: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/components/dashboard/filter-bar.tsx`**

- Search input (debounced, 300ms)
- Filter dropdowns: Status, Country, Research Area (populated from existing data)
- Sort dropdown
- All filter state managed with `useState` -- no URL params needed for localStorage app
- Passes filter/sort config up to parent via callback or uses a shared state approach

Architecture decision: Use a simple `useReducer` in the dashboard page to hold filter state, pass it down. No need for global state management.

### 2.6 -- Professor List and Card

**File: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/components/dashboard/professor-list.tsx`**

- Reads all professors via `useStorageData(() => storage.professors.getAll())`
- Applies filters and sorting from props
- Renders a grid of `ProfessorCard` components
- Empty state when no professors exist

**File: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/components/dashboard/professor-card.tsx`**

- Card showing: name, university, department, country, research areas as badges, status badge, last contact
- Clicking navigates to `/professor/[id]`
- Quick status dropdown to change status inline
- Uses `Link` from `next/link`

**File: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/components/dashboard/status-badge.tsx`**

- Reusable component: takes an `ApplicationStatus`, renders a colored badge
- Uses the color map from `constants.ts`

**File: `/Users/shakirulhkhan/Documents/Developer/experiments/profreach/components/dashboard/dashboard-stats.tsx`**

- Row of stat cards at the top: Total Professors, Emails Sent, Responses, etc.
- Computed from professor list statuses

### Commit: "feat: implement dashboard with professor list, filtering, and AI lookup"

